	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 11th 9:47 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>K, I've been playing a ranger and a rogue for quite some time now on the Prexus server. The ranger being my first and main, I got him up to level 26, before I ended him. Main reason was cause I found him too weak. He was a good soloer, but with the snare/DD/archery technique, it would take forever for me to level. All my real life friends, and friends that I have made in groups have constantly gone passed me in levels, and I simply lost interest in the character, when I'd have to make new friends and regroup with new people on a daily basis.<br><br>My rogue I still play cause to me, it's one of the most fun class to play. Especially a dwarven rogue =P. The roleplaying just makes it great for that race/combo. The class is a quick leveler and I brought him to level 18 in a few days (course, he was semi-twinked).<br><br>Now, I'm deciding to delete my ranger, cause I haven't played him in about 3 months. I was looking into other classes to play. I've basically tried every class to an extent (about 6th level), and decided to try the wizard. Now it appealed to me at first, and right now, it's still fun to play (still level 6). But asking those of higher levels, is there more to the wizard?<br><br>I mean, is every battle that I fight in going to have the same general pattern?:<br><br>nuke<br>nuke<br>med<br>/gems<br>repeat<br><br>And even more, when I first looked at the spell line, my first impression was "wow." But after playing this class a bit, it seemed there wasn't any new spice to any of the spells. As the level increases, it seems as if the only thing changes is the damage in our nukes, and the places we port.<br><br>Asking some veteran wizard to try and inform me of what else a wizard can do, or what else makes the class fun for them.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
