<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=990543090336></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f990543090336><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=990543090336>RE: are wizards fun?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=990543090336#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=46723><span id=Scholar>gdnom</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>62 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, May 22nd 10:51 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.28]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I think so.<br><br>Leveled it to 29 now. <br><br>It has it's ups and dows just like any other class.<br><br>Tell you one thing about this class...&nbsp;&nbsp;Nothing is more exhilirating once you see a giant down to 50% hitpoints.  Then you cast your most powerful nuke at that level.., then it turns around and run.<br><br>Of course if you make a mistake and cast it above 50%... the meleer's will have a hell of a time making up for the 230+ points of damage you just did at level 29 just to get that mob off of you.  And if you were casting some stuns before that...  it's almost impossible to take agro off and you will almost certainly die.<br><br>At times you'll be reminded of the Ranger.  Quick damage, low hitpoints.  But at least Rangers get sow.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
