<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98978108757307></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98978108757307><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98978108757307>RE: are wizards fun?</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=11&mid=98978108757307#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=13945><span id= >Rathiel</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>14 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, May 13th 3:11 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, I'm only a veteran to 24, but to this point its still fun.&nbsp;&nbsp;It may be that same general pattern, nuke nuke med etc., but you need to learn when to nuke, when to stun, roots, etc.  In other words, when grouped there is quite a bit of thought that goes into what you do at any given time.  If your going to solo quite a bit, then its just that pattern until you can quad kite at 29.  Plus, by 24 you get your gate spells to everywhere but velious.  I can't tell you how nice it is to not have to run anywhere.  Just my 2cp.<br><br>Qaos Starfury<br>24th Circle Wizard<br>Druizzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
